05/07/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul is in Washington Wednesday (5 July) for a meeting with US counterpart Condoleezza Rice and National Security Adviser Stephen Hadley. Prior to his departure Tuesday, Gul said his visit would be aimed at boosting bilateral ties. Turkey's EU membership bid and attacks by Kurdish terrorists based in Iraq are high on the agenda.
In other news, a small bomb went off Tuesday in a building used by the ruling Justice and Development party in Istanbul. The explosion caused minor damage but no casualties. (Anadolu Agency - 05/07/06; AFP, TurkishPress.com, AP - 04/07/06)
